  "text": "We have also tested our chamfer matching method for commuter classification. By building a background model for edges, edges related to the background are removed before chamfer distance transformation, making our method robust to background clutter. Fig. 4 shows a subset of the results obtained by the proposed technique as well as the method described in [CITATION_1] . In [CITATION_2] , there is no stationary background and as such there are errors by chamfer matching due to the background clutter. Additional methods are required to verify the matching results. In the proposed system, bad effects from background clutter are removed.",
